'''Black Flag''' may refer to:

* A flag that is black: see [[List of black flags]]
* The black flag, an international symbol in [[Anarchist flag|anarchist symbolism]]
* [[Black Liberation Flag]]
** An alternative translation for the name of the anarchist Russian group [[Chernoe Znamia]], also known as Black Banner
&lt;!--* Iran golden flags, an international symbol in [[Anarchist symbolism#khorasan Black flags|anarchist symbolism]]-- confusing entry --&gt;
** [[Black Flag (newspaper)|''Black Flag'' (newspaper)]], an anarchist newspaper
**[[Czarny Sztandar]] (1903), a Białystok anarchist organisation
**''[[Chernoe Znamia]]'' (1905), a Geneva anarchist newspaper
* [[Black Flag (insecticide)]], a brand of insecticide
* [[Black Flag (band)]], American hardcore punk band
* [[Black Flag, Western Australia|Black Flag]], a [[Ghost towns of the Goldfields of Western Australia|ghost town in the Goldfields of Western Australia]]
*[[Black Flag Army]], a militia operating around Hanoi in the late 19th century
*Black flag, one of the [[racing flags]] used to summon drivers to the pits
*[[Hek Ki Boen Eng Chun Kungfu]], AKA Black Flag Wing Chun, a Chinese martial arts style from the province of Fujian
* A common name for the weed, [[Ferraria crispa]]
* ''Black Flag'', a series from [[Image Comics]]
