      <text xml:space="preserve">{{Redirect|Beda}}
{{Other uses}}

{{Infobox saint
|name=Saint Bede the Venerable
|birth_date=ca. 673&lt;ref name=ASEEncBede/&gt;
|death_date={{Death date|df=yes|735|5|26}}
|feast_day=25 May (Western Churches) &lt;br&gt; 27 May (Orthodox Church and [[General Roman Calendar]], between 1899&amp;ndash;1969)
|venerated_in=[[Roman Catholic Church]], [[Eastern Orthodox Church]], [[Anglican Communion]], [[Lutheran Church]]
|image=The Venerable Bede translates John 1902.jpg
|imagesize=220 px
|caption=&quot;The Venerable Bede Translates John&quot; by J. D. Penrose (ca 1902)
|birth_place= near Sunderland&lt;ref name=ASEEncBede/&gt;
|death_place=[[Jarrow]], [[Northumbria]]&lt;ref name=ASEEncBede/&gt;
|titles=[[Doctor of the Church]], [[Monk]], [[Historian]]
|beatified_date=
|beatified_place=
|beatified_by=
|canonized_date=1899 recognised as [[Doctor of the Church]]
|canonized_place=Rome
|canonized_by=[[Pope Leo XIII]]
|patronage=[[List of English writers|English writers]] and [[historian]]s; [[Jarrow]]
|major_shrine=[[Durham Cathedral]].
